Definition.WordDefinition: Initially \In*i"tial*ly\, adv. In an initial or incipient manner or degree; at the beginning. --Barrow. [1913 Webster]
initially adv : at the beginning; "at first he didn't notice anything strange" [syn: {ab initio}, {at first}, {at the start}]
